metadata.description:
Niels presents the paper “Thousand-Brains Systems: Sensorimotor Intelligence for Rapid, Robust Learning and Inference” also known as the capabilities paper.

Read the paper here: https://arxiv.org/abs/2507.04494
A plain language explainer: https://thousandbrains.org/thousand-brain-systems-sensorimotor-intelligence-for-rapid-robust-learning-and-inference-a-plain-language-explainer/ 

00:00 Introduction
02:54 Monty Architecture
05:29 Monty and Movement
05:54 Learning in Monty
06:28 Inference in Monty
08:37 Dataset for Learning
09:42 Robust Inference
14:44 Structured Object Representations
22:19 Invariance, Equivariance and Symmetry
32:24 Rapid Inference
33:37 Model Free Action Policies
34:23 Model Based Action Policies
40:14 Using Models for Behavior
41:32 Voting
48:29 Rapid, Continual, Efficient Learning
49:14 Few Shot Learning
52:47 Rapid Learning: Generalization
56:08 Continual Learning
58:24 Continual Learning Performance
01:02:18 Continual Learning Robustness
01:03:20 Computational Efficiency
01:04:26 FLOPs at Learning
01:05:26 FLOPs at Inference
01:09:03 Emergent Properties of Sensorimotor Systems
01:11:36 Future Research
01:13:01 Future Applications
